"I hope your country will be recognized by the United Nations soon", said Russian parliament member Alexei Ostrovskiy, toasting a glass of vodka.
The opposition, which was represented in the elections by former Vice President Raul Khadzhimba and two businessmen Zaus Ardzinba and Beslan Boutba, criticized the agreements made last year with Moscow, such as the one that allows Russia to control the railway network of Abkhazia for 10 years.
