Under Master 2 (M2), they take an entrance exam at the beginning of the year, focusing on their field, and at the end of the year, another exam, to certify their ability to teach, the Minister explained.
They will participate in professional internships during the second year of the Master's degree and will present their students as a professor-intern during the first year.
If you add up all the internships that you'll be offered before the admissions process, you'll gain more experience with students, almost 300 hours, he continued.
The minister also announced that he would propose a "personal right to education", which does not yet exist in national education.
He reaffirmed the project to abolish the school map by 2012.
At the elite École normale supérieure, the experts have 15 minutes to convince the public about climate change.
Fifteen minutes to present the objectives of the Copenhagen Summit: this is the call announced on Saturday morning by Jean Jouzel, Vice-President of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (GIEC), at the initiative of the Ecole normale supérieure in Ulm.
As a journalist reported to AFP, Nobel Peace Prize winner Jean Jouzel opened the first of the "Ernest" conferences, a one-day seminar consisting of 15-minute expert presentations that will be filmed and open to the public.
We wanted to do something that would draw people in and make them want to learn more, explained 22-year-old Edouard Hannezo, one of the organisers of the seminar, which was named after a fish from a local pond, which had been named by the students.
