Delays in payments: anger at prison guards, planned action
The prison guards' unions announced a "general mobilization" on Friday, demanding that they be paid their Christmas bonuses and overtime, which for financial reasons had been postponed until January.
The Prison FO (2nd Guards) asked staff who will not be on duty to participate in the demonstration held on Tuesday morning outside the prison facilities to "block" them and warn them of "the theft of their wages".
The CGT for the prison guards (3rd sector) called on them to "convene a meeting in each prison and initiate a major mobilization" saying that it was "shameful and unacceptable" that "overtime and overtime for night work, Sundays and holidays" worked in October were not paid in December.
